cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the problem of building fastest broadcast trees in delay-tolerant networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of distributed algorithms and graph theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper deals with temporal distances and scheduling, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
